README for DarkSUSY
===================

* For compiling and installing instructions, read README.INSTALL

* If you want to develop code for DarkSUSY, read README.DEVELOPER

If you use this code, please refer to it as:

P. Gondolo, J. Edsjö, P. Ullio, L. Bergstöm, M. Schelke and E.A. Baltz,
JCAP 07 (2004) 008 [astro-ph/0406204]; P. Gondolo, J. Edsjö, P. Ullio, 
L. Bergström, M. Schelke, E.A. Baltz, T. Bringmann and G. Duda, 
http://www.physto.se/~edsjo/darksusy

Most of the routines in DarkSUSY are based upon original physics work
published separately. Please also refer to those when you
use them. Below are some of the main publications behind different
routines in DarkSUSY (if you use the default options).

* General MSSM routines:
    L. Bergstrom and P. Gondolo, Astrop. Phys. 5 (1996) 263.

* Relic density:
    P. Gondolo and G. Gelmini, Nucl. Phys. B360 (1991) 145.
    J. Edsjo and P. Gondolo, Phys. Rev. D56 (1997) 1879.
    J. Edsjo, M. Schelke, P. Ullio and P. Gondolo,
    JCAP 04 (2003) 001.

* Direct detection:
    L. Bergstrom and P. Gondolo, Astrop. Phys. 5 (1996) 263.

* Neutrino telescopes:
    L. Bergstrom, J. Edsjo and P. Gondolo, Phys. Rev. D58 (1998) 103519.

* Positrons:
    E.A. Baltz and J. Edsjo, Phys. Rev. D59 (1999) 023511.

* Antiprotons:
    L. Bergstrom, J. Edsjo and P. Ullio, Astrophys. J. 526 (1999) 215.

* Gamma lines
    L. Bergstrom and P. Ullio, Nucl. Phys. B504 (1997) 27.
    P. Ullio and L. Bergstrom, Phys. Rev. D57 (1998) 1962.

* Internal bremsstrahlung
    T. Bringmann, L. Bergstrom and J. Edsjo, JHEP 0801 (2008) 049.    

* Cont. gammas from the halo:
    L. Bergstrom, J. Edsjo and P. Ullio, Phys. Rev. D58 (1998) 083507.

* Kinetic decoupling and microhalos
    T. Bringmann and S. Hofmann, JCAP 0407 (2007) 16;
    T. Bringmann, NJP 11 (2009) 10527.

* FeynHiggs: For Higgs masses
    See the FeynHiggs web page for information on how to refer to it.

* HiggsBounds: For Higgs limits from accelerators
    See HiggsBounds web page for information on how to refer to it.

* Isasugra: for mSUGRA
    See the isajet web page for information on how to refer to it.

* SLHALIB: for reading/writing SLHA files
    See the slhalib web page for information on how to refer to it.

Note that this list is far from complete, so you will most likely have
to consider also referring other work depending on how you use DarkSUSY.
